After that, we adjusted the data for covariates, including sex, batch, and sequencing quality metrics (Additional file 2: Table S1). Given the large number of sequencing quality features, we performed principal component analysis (PCA) on these data and found that the first two PCs on the unstandardized features explained nearly 99% of the variance. Consequently, we opted to use two sequencing surrogate variables (seqSV1 and seqSV2) as covariates. We applied a linear model to remove the confounding factors:
